DescriptionData.Title: Instant Miracles DVD
DescriptionData.Description: Miracle-making made easy! With the techniques and methods explained on Instant Miracles, you will learn classic, stunning magic tricks - easily. This broadcast quality DVD teaches you how to conjure with items found around the house, at a restaurant or even in your pocket. No special props and no complicated sleight of hand are required. Each effect was selected because it is both unfathomable and is easy to perform, even for beginning magicians. It is this combination of easy-to-do yet powerful tricks that makes Instant Miracles an excellent introduction to the fascinating world of magic. On this DVD you will learn: Mindreading via cell phone, how to levitate a borrowed pencil, to pull a coin through a spectator's tightly clenched fist, how to cut and restore an unprepared length of rope, to predict the numbers on three randomly-rolled dice, and much more! Danny Orleans is one of magic's most gifted teachers. He performs and explains the classic secrets on Instant Miracles. Each effect is described in crystal clear detail, leaving no questions unanswered. Even if you've never studied magic, Danny will guide you through the learning process with the care and experience that decades of teaching magic - to budding magicians of all ages - has given him.
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Teaches classic magic tricks for beginners

DescriptionData.Title: The Magic Ingredient & Kidology DVD
DescriptionData.Description:
Now available on DVD, it's The Magic Ingredient and Kidology! This disc contains two complete programs, for 100 minutes of Sammy's quality kid-show performance and demonstration!
The Magic Ingredient - How to Be a Kid-Show Celebrity! How to Be a Kid-Show Celebrity! What's the magic ingredient in a successful kid-show? In his first video ever, Samuel Patrick Smith answers that question. Enjoy a live performance of solid kid-show comedy and magic, followed by a studio session where you'll learn not only the method of the trick, but the hidden tips and secrets behind making each one a hit in your own show. Don't miss Sammy's routine with Puff the Magic Rabbit!
The Magic Ingredient features: The Crystal Tube, Crayons to Scarf, Multiplying Balls, The Imagination Cap, The Shrinking Glove, Headband Blendo, Egg Bag, Nest of Boxes, and Puff the Magic Rabbit.
Kidology - The Science of Making Kids Laugh. Step into Sammy Smith's laboratory and watch successful demonstrations of laugh-packed magic for kids. It's been reduced to a science! Every routine comes to you direct from Sammy's action-packed kid-show, followed by studio explanations - fully tested, polished, and ready to adapt to your own personal performances.
Kidology features: The Invisible Flying Scarf, Soft Soap, Portable Beach Balls, Cut & Restored Rope, Monster Hat, and Commercials and Jokes. The Magic Ingredient and Kidology. 100 minutes.
These two programs originally sold for $60 together - now available on one fully searchable DVD for one low price!
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Includes two complete programs, for 100 minutes of Sammy's quality kid-show performance and demonstration

DescriptionData.Title: Miracles with a Marked Deck DVD
DescriptionData.Description: Magic with a marked deck has never been easier to learn! On this DVD, professional magician Kirk Charles explores the workings of a marked deck and demonstrates its use in over one dozen stunning tricks. From mind reading effects to supposed demonstrations of super-skills, Charles shows how this subtle yet powerful magical tool can be developed into a devious secret weapon in any magicians bag of tricks. You will learn how to instantly memorize the order of the entire deck, tell the difference between black and red cards - apparently by weight alone, analyze a spectators handwriting as if you were an expert graphologist, determine the name of a spectators selected card - before even he knows its identity, and much more! In addition to tricks, Charles discusses the psychology behind working with a marked deck and how to conceal its presence from an audience. Years of careful study and practice are laid bare on Miracles with a Marked Deck. Charles also talks about the history and background of marked decks, and the development of modern marking systems including the popular Boris Wild Marked Deck (see below). Kirk Charles is a professional magician living in Seattle, Washington.
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Professional magician Kirk Charles explores the workings of a marked deck and demonstrates its use in over one dozen stunning tricks in this DVD

DescriptionData.Title: Twist With Sam Gospel DVD
DescriptionData.Description: The Gospel edition of Twist with Sam is a fun, cool and interactive balloon instructional video with international twister Sam Tee ("Uncle Button"). On this DVD you will learn simple twist and techniques to create interesting Bible stories. The Cross, Heart, Sword, and Flower are used many times as props to illustrate a bible story as well as to talk about verses. This is a highly recommended DVD for any Gospel Twister. Sam teaches his routines for a Cross with two hearts, and 5 Petals of God's Flower. He tells the stories of David, Christ's Birth, Jonah, Shorty on a tree, and The Armor Of God. The armor routine dresses the child in helmet, shield, breastplate, belt, sword, and shoes. Most of the balloons Sam uses is the 260Q Jewel Tones, and Red, White, and Pink 6 inch Hearts.
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Teaches simple bible story balloon designs

DescriptionData.Title: Twist With Sam DVD - Vol 3
DescriptionData.Description: More Fun with Balloons! Learn to twist and sculpt more than 25 balloon designs with international twister Sam Tee ("Uncle Button"), ideal for the beginner and advanced. Volume 3 includes: Funny snake, Rose Bud, Candle Lamp, Baby Elephant, Froggy, Lobster, Guardian Angel, Blooming Flower, Turtle Bracelet, Penguin, Lion, Clown Fish, Fishing Reel, Doggie, Helicopter, Happy Clown, Ladybug Bracelet, Beary Cute, Spidey, Dragonfly, Bubble crown, Basecap, M&M hat (Mickey), M&M hat (Minnie), and Bunny Hat. Special Bonus: How to twist without a knot: Bubble Sword, Swan, Sword, Lover Swan, Mr. and Mrs. Smiley, Heart Within A Heart, Flower Bracelet, Balloon Holder, Geo Blossom Flower and Heart with a holder.
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Teaches more than 25 balloon sculpture designs

DescriptionData.Title: Fair Organ Follies CD
DescriptionData.Description:
Amusement parks in the early 1900's entertained patrons with music either by live bands, or automatic 'fair organs' like this one - a 57-key Gavioli built in Paris, ca. 1905. DescriptionData.Title: Vanishing Cane Magic Trick
DescriptionData.Description: You twirl a cane between your fingers and even tap it on the floor to prove it's solid. While you hold the cane on each end, it instantaneously changes into two large silks (not included) or vanishes altogether! You will also need two (18 inch silks) or 24 inch silks to perform this effect.

DescriptionData.Title: Tootsie Pops
DescriptionData.Description: One at a time, four Tootsie Roll pops are pulled from a bag, showing four different flavors. Pick two flavors for yourself to keep and hand the bag with the remaining two to a spectator. But then? They have disappeared! Magically they are in the other bag along with your pops! Now all four are handed out for audience to enjoy! Such a massive upgrade from the old flat plastic lollipop trick! An online demonstration video makes it easier!
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Includes a bag and four Tootsie Roll pops

DescriptionData.Title: Santa in the Chimney Silk Routine
DescriptionData.Description: This occupies no space but works great! Includes a large decorated house silk and a smaller Santa silk. Ideal for a beautiful routine in silks. The Santa vanishes into the chimney but where? Maybe he got stuck! Magically, you pull him out but he's covered in soot! And where are the gifts? They're in the bag that you showed empty before you started. This can be done your way, using thumbtips, change bag, etc. An online demonstration video makes it easier!
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Ideal for a beautiful routine in silks.
It occupies no space but plays great!
Includes a large decorated house silk and a smaller Santa silk.

DescriptionData.Title: Popcorn Dye Magic Box
DescriptionData.Description: This great utility item has so many uses. A cardboard popcorn box is shown empty. Suddenly, silks are magically produced from it! It can also be used to vanish silks or make them change color. Other small items can also be used in the box. The perfect vanish for (20th Century Silks).
DescriptionData.BulletPoint: Magic item disappearing and re-appearing popcorn box

DescriptionData.Title: Egg Nest Magic Trick
DescriptionData.Description: This colorful and eye-catching trick makes a great impact - everyone likes to the chance to win something for free! Show your audience five colorful plastic Easter eggs, and slip a gold coin, dollar bill or a ring into the one of the eggs (without showing which color egg has the item). Four people are invited to reach into the bag without looking and remove an egg, and you take the last egg. Of course the egg left for you is the one with the the valuables! Also a great way to give something special to the birthday child. Directions and ideas included. Very easy to do. Need some (Silly Rings)?
